<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-326-293  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 326 293.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Feb 5 1990 v36 n1795 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD budget cuts key projects. (US Department of Defense)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The 1991 budget for the US Department of Defense totals $295billion and calls for the termination or phasing out of more than12 key programs, including GTE's Mobile Subscriber Equipment(MSE), the ITT/Westinghouse Airborne Self-Protective Jammer(ASPJ), McDonnell Douglas's AH-64 attack helicopter and F-15Efighter and General Dynamics' M-1 tank.andP;  Program terminations willsave the DOD $3 billion; termination of the programs will save$28.3 billion over the next five years.andP;  The budget calls for $38billion to go to research, development, test and evaluation, $4.47billion for the Strategic Defense Initiative programs, and $1.2billion for unidentified Pentagon anti-drug efforts.andP;  The budgetwas originally factored at 3.3 percent inflation and had to beadjusted to a 4.2 percent factor.andP;  Program funding had to be cuteven further than expected to meet the higher inflation figures.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefenseMilitaryGovernment AgencyBudgeting.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraphtable.andO;Caption:   Research, development, test and evaluation for FY 1991. (graph)Funding for major defense projects. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>